rename.to: Exception while loading session in weeklies

body: This is being worked on, should be fixed in the next weekly.

Thanks! Please, let me know when ready
It seems we fail here:

04:31:11 8800 [ZAP-ProxyThread-2] INFO org.parosproxy.paros.control.Control  - Session file opened
@hnestorova this should not prevent ZAP from working - are you actually having any problems with ZAP?

@psiinon  what I have noticed in addition to the NPEs in the logs is the following:

Before the version upgrade, for one of our recorded clean sessions we got 2 high alerts:
```
Source Code Disclosure -   File Inclusion
http://PRIVATE/PRIVATE/resources/get?id=JS&ver=655406725
--
SQL Injection
GET : http://PRIVATE/PRIVATE/login.jsp?%2FPRIVATE%2F=+AND+1%3D1+--+
```
Then, after the upgrade, the high alerts disappeared. Yesterday, I recorded again the session, run the Jenkins job and got one of the two alerts types:
```
SQL Injection 

GET   : http://PRIVATE/PRIVATE/login.jsp?%2FPRIVATE=&userName=USER+AND+1%3D1+--+
--
```

Today, after our daily run of the tests and with no fixes from our side, the high alert is again not present

Yes, that can happen.
For complex real world apps the ZAP spidering is not completely deterministic - sometimes some urls will be found in one scan and not in another. Thats because of timing issues and because apps change over time.
You should investigate any issues found to see if they are real issues or false positives.
Ideally you should examine the URLs found and compare see how effectively ZAP is exploring your app. If its missing significant parts then see if tuning ZAP helps, and/or reporting the problem to us of course.

@psiinon yes, this sounds reasonable
the problem, however, is that with the previous version we had the same exceptions each day + maybe some new ones. But the SQL Injection and Source Code Disclosure -   File Inclusion were known to us and they did get caught every day while after the upgrade this is not the case. So i am not sure how to approach this.
No matter what it is itâ€™s not related to the issue this ticket is for. Please take the discussion of this second topic to the [user group](https://groups.google.com/g/zaproxy-users).

sure , I will.
I was just answering the questions by psiinon

issue.title: Fix exception while loading session

repository.name: zaproxy
repository.description: The ZAP by Checkmarx Core project

issue.body:
Change `SiteMap` to not try to get the leaf name when finding a branch
(e.g. no method).
Change `Session` to fail earlier if the required parameters are not
provided when getting the leaf name.

Fix #6265.
